                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#00" n="#">Fol. 170vb: Ownership note.</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 170vb: ዝቅዳሴ፡ ዘአቡነ፡ ወልደ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወወልዱ፡ ገብረ፡ ሚካኤል፡</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 170vb: This is a Missal of ˀabunä Wäldä Śəllase, and his son (is) Gäbrä Mikaˀel.</q>
                           <p part="N"/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#00" n="#">Fol. 172va-vb: Donation note extended by a genealogy of the donor.</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"> Fol. 172va-vb: አቡነ፡ ተላዌ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወለደ፡ አቡነ፡ ንዋየ፡ ማርያም፡ ኃይለ፡ ማርያም፡ ወለተ፡ ቀለምሲስ፡ ወለደ፡ ወለተ፡ ቀለምሲስ፡ አቡነ፡ ወልደ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወለደት፡ ወልደ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ገብረ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወእኁሁ፡ ኃይለ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወወልዱ፡ ወልዱ[sic]፡ ወልደ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወምስለ፡ ብእ[fol. 172vb]ሲቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ሕይወት፡ ወምስለ፡ እሙ፡ ኡጽፍተ፡ ድንግል፡ ወምስለ፡ እኅቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ኪዳን፡ ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘተሳየጣ፡ በንዋዩ፡ አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ዘወሐቦ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ሰጣ[sic]፡ ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘፈሐቃ፡ ወዘተአገላ፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ይኩን፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።[fol. 173r] ከመ፡ ይኩኖሙ፡ መርሐ፡ መንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 172va-vb: ˀabunä Tälawe Krǝstos begot ˀabunä Nǝwayä Maryam, Ḫaylä Maryam, Wälättä Qälämsis, he begot (them). Wälättä Qälämsis begot ˀabunä Wäldä Śǝllase, Wäldä Śǝllase Gäbrä Mikaˀel and his brother Ḫaylä Mikaˀel, and his son Wäldä Mikaˀel, with his wife Wälättä Ḥǝywät, and with his mother ˀUṣǝftä Dǝngǝl, and with his sister Wälättä Kidan. ˀAbunä Gäbrä Mikaˀel bought this book with his own money and donated it to (the tabot of) St. Michael of Säṭa. He who stole it or erased (its text) shall be excommunicated by the authority of Peter and Paul, for ever and ever, amen. So that it might be for them a guide (to) the Kingdom of Heaven.</q>
                           <p part="N"/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <locus target="#00"> Fols. 183ra-185vb; 1va-2vb; 122vb-124vb; 171ra-172rb: Anaphora of St. Basil of Caesarea.</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p part="N"/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Crude notes (writing exercises): fols. 1r, 2r, 4r.&#xD;
- Pen trial, in red ink: fol. 1v, in the bottom margin.&#xD;
- Omitted passages written in the margin (sometimes the place the passages belongs to is indicated by the tämälläs-sigh in the shape of the cross, written in the text column; but sometimes there is no visible sign): fols. 5r, 9v, 97r, 141r, in the upper margin, 24ra, in the bottom margin, etc.&#xD;
- Crude notes (both recent and older): fols. 8r, 40r, 41r, 44r, 46r, 47v, etc., in the upper margin.&#xD;
- Extensive crude notes (apparently writing exercise): fols. 83v-84r, in the bottom margin.&#xD;
- The names of the donors are also indicated in supplication formulas within the text of the Ms. (s. fols. 7vb-8ra, 26vb, 28vb, etc.).</item>
